phase2.explanation:
You didn't check if an instance already exists. This can cause duplicate singletons.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void Awake()
{
    if (instance == null)
    {
        instance = this;
        DontDestroyOnLoad(gameObject);
    }
    else if (instance != this)
    {
        Destroy(gameObject);
    }
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check if an instance already exists. Otherwise, you'll end up with duplicates and unexpected behavior."
